<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="398" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,616,2041]" pageId="1" pageNumber="398">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,268,653,677]" pageId="1" pageNumber="398">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from the other Neotropical species by the following combination of features: (1) lateral ocellus separated from compound eye by about 0.3× maximum ocellar diameter (vs. continuous to the compound eyes), (2) mesopleuron dark brown or black (vs. orange-brown in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gauld" authorityYear="1988" box="[931,1047,726,749]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Eremotylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tropicus">
<emphasis box="[931,1047,726,749]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="398">E. tropicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and green in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Townes" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[1193,1337,726,749]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Eremotylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vitripennis">
<emphasis box="[1193,1337,726,749]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="398">E. vitripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and (3) posterior transverse carina of mesosternum complete (vs. present only laterally in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gauld" authorityYear="1988" box="[1026,1142,762,785]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Eremotylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tropicus">
<emphasis box="[1026,1142,762,785]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="398">E. tropicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
